column1: #Text=Fort Smith is in northwest Arkansas and borders Oklahoma .
#Text=It is the county seat of Sebastian County .
#Text=The city has a population of 80,286 which makes it the second largest city in Arkansas behind Little Rock .
#Text=It is located in the River Valley of Arkansas between the Ouachita mountains in the south and the Boston and Ozark mountains of the north and a gateway city to the Ozarks .
#Text=In 1817 Fort Smith was established as a military fort next to Indian territory in Oklahoma to keep the peace between the native Osage tribes and the recently relocated Cherokee groups .
#Text=It is at the junction of the Arkansas river and the Poteau river at a place that early French explorers called Belle Point .
#Text=The military fort was named after General Thomas A. Smith , the military 's district commander .

#Text=The military later relocated to nearby Fort Chaffee but the civilian settlers remained keeping the name of the fort and establishing a western frontier town that was often the last genteel layover for people from all walks of life before excursions into Indian Oklahoma including soldiers en route to the Mexican War in the Southwest .
#Text=Later Fort Smith became a popular stop for westward expansionists , gold rush diggers , and those seeking better opportunities due to the Great Depression and Dust Bowl of the 20th century .

#Text=Today as the second largest city in the state , the municipality and surrounding area is a major economic hub for the state of Arkansas with many major corporations with roots in the city still in operation and employing thousands .
#Text=The downtown area and commercial zones are usually busy with voluminous traffic most days but beyond that you will find quiet residential zones and woods .
#Text=Due to economic trends in the U.S. economy , some major factories and plants have closed and/or moved resulting in a swelling of the unemployed population and an uptick in local taxes .
#Text=Service by American Eagle from Dallas/Fort Worth , and Delta Connection from Atlanta .
#Text=Northwest Arkansas Regional Airport ( XNA ) near Bentonville , is about an hour and a half from Fort Smith .
#Text=Tulsa International Airport ( TUL ) ( in Oklahoma ) and Little Rock International Airport ( LIT ) are both about a two-hour drive away .
#Text=Fort Smith does not have passenger rail service .

#Text=The nearest cities with Amtrak stations are Oklahoma City , which is the northern terminus of the Heartland Flyer to Fort Worth ; and Little Rock , which is served by the Texas Eagle San Antonio - Chicago route .
#Text=Fort Smith is at the intersection of Interstate 40 , Interstate 540 , and US Route 71 .
#Text=Approximate driving times are : 2 hours and 30 minutes west of Little Rock , 1 hour south of Fayetteville , and 3 hours east of Oklahoma City .
#Text=The Jefferson Lines provides bus service to the east , west and north .
#Text=The best way to get around and see Fort Smith is by car .
#Text=Also , public transport is provided by Fort Smith Transit .
#Text=Although Fort Smith is Arkansas ' second largest city , it is relatively compact and getting around should n't be much of a problem .
#Text=Miss Laura 's Social Club and Visitor Center , 2 N " B " St. , +1 479 783-8888 , A house of ill-repute from Fort Smith 's past , now a visitor center .
#Text=It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places .
#Text=This is a good starting point for any visit to Fort Smith .
#Text=Fort Smith National Historic Site , South of Garrison Ave. , near the Arkansas river .
#Text=Parking and Park entrance near 3rd St. and Garland Ave.
#Text=This site includes the original Fort sites and the reconstructed gallows of Hanging Judge Issac Parker .
#Text=Take a ride on the trolley past the Judge Parker court and the National Historic Site .
#Text=Belle Grove Historic District , 22 square block area north of downtown , On the National Register of Historic Places and has 25 restored historical homes .
#Text=Fort Chaffee and Chaffee Crossing , Hwy 22 ( east of Fort Smith ) Former military fort with a rich history .
#Text=Elvis Presley was inducted into the military and started basic training there .
#Text=The movies Biloxi Blues , and A Soldier 's Story were filmed there .
#Text=Arkansas ' largest bowling facility , with a whopping 72 lanes .
#Text=An ordinary roller skating rink , but with a unique distinction : it has the only artistic roller skating club in Arkansas .
#Text=The largest free air show in the United States held every October .
#Text=University of Arkansas — Fort Smith , 5210 Grand Ave. , +1 479 788-7000
#Text=There are several major employers in Fort Smith , including Baldor Electric , Whirlpool Corporation , Rheem , Golden Ventures and Arkansas Best Corporation ( ABF ) .
